9 An Act relating to agriculture; requiring persons
entering certain areas to maintain position of the
10 gate at use; prescribing penalties for violation;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
11 codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-34 of Title 2, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Any individual entering through gates used for ingress or
19 egress to a property designated as an easement shall maintain the
20 position of the gate upon use.
21 B. 1. Any individual who violates the provisions of subsection
22 A of this section shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
23 punishable by a fine not more than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
