2 or by both such fine and imprisonment.
3 2. Any individual convicted of a second offense shall, upon
4 conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine not more
5 than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), by imprisonment in a county
6 jail for not more than one hundred eighty (180) days, or by both
7 such fine and imprisonment.
8 3. Any individual convicted of a third or subsequent offense
9 shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine not more than One
10 Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($1,500.00), by imprisonment in a
11 county jail for not more than one (1) year, or by both such fine and
12 imprisonment.
13 4. Any individual convicted pursuant to the provisions of this
14 subsection shall also be liable for damages.
15 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
16 shall promulgate rules necessary to implement the provisions of this
17 act.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
